Add a transition property that changes the background color in 5 seconds.
[!raw!]
{0}: {1} 
      {2} ease-in;

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The Transition Property [/h1]

In the example below, the div element has width and height of 50px, with a green background. We specified a transition effect for the width property, with a duration of 3 seconds:

The CSS will look like this: [code format="css" codeId="620"]div {
   width: 50px;
   height: 50px;
   background: #32CD32;
   [b]transition: width 3s;[/b]
}
div:hover {
   [b]width: 250px;[/b]
}[/code]
If you hover over the div element, it will move from left to right. [img id="2706" width="100%"]
[note]When the cursor is moused out of the element, it will gradually change back to its original style.[/note]
